Project Overview

The AI Semiconductor Trade Intelligence System (ASTIS) is an AI-assisted Business Intelligence solution built in Microsoft Excel that analyzes global semiconductor trade patterns, geopolitical risks, supplier concentration, technology specialization, and strategic sourcing opportunities.

This project transforms raw trade data into executive-level dashboards that help decision-makers identify critical supply chain dependencies, monitor geopolitical exposure, and support strategic investment decisions.

Unlike traditional Excel dashboards that only visualize data, this project focuses on generating business insights and executive recommendations using data-driven analysis.

🎯 Business Problem

The global semiconductor industry is one of the world's most critical supply chains. Rising geopolitical tensions, export controls, supplier concentration, and logistics disruptions have increased the need for data-driven decision-making.

Organizations require an analytical system capable of answering questions such as:

Which countries dominate semiconductor exports?
Which suppliers are strategically important?
Which trade routes create supply chain risks?
Which semiconductor technologies dominate global trade?
How concentrated is the global semiconductor ecosystem?
What strategic actions should organizations take to reduce supply chain risk?

This project addresses these challenges by developing an interactive executive intelligence dashboard using Microsoft Excel.

🎯 Project Objectives
Analyze global semiconductor trade flows.
Identify leading exporting and importing countries.
Measure trade concentration across countries, suppliers, and technologies.
Detect geopolitical risks within semiconductor supply chains.
Evaluate strategic supplier importance.
Identify technology specialization by country.
Generate AI-assisted executive insights.
Deliver an interactive Business Intelligence dashboard for decision-makers.

